# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-HARDEN-03G

Title
Canonical verification model, metadata typing completion, and salvage classification cleanup

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Introduce a single canonical typed verification/recovery model, eliminate remaining dynamic metadata construction from core paths, bind reporting/output to that model, and clear the carried-forward salvage metadata classification lint so the hardening sequence can proceed on a truthful, deterministic foundation.

This packet exists because:

- CRUSHR-HARDEN-03A improved API/public-surface truth, but full contraction was deferred because current in-repo consumers still depend on `crushr::format` and `crushr::index_codec`
- a pre-existing clippy failure remains in the salvage metadata classification flow
- core metadata/output paths still risk drift unless the system converges on one canonical typed model

This is a canonical-model and typed-metadata packet.
It is not a feature-expansion packet.

